<TITLE> Cyclone 'Ward' slightly weakens in the Bay </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 13 (bdnews24.com)  Cyclone 'Ward' hovering over the Bay of Bengal became slightly weak on Sunday morning and turned into a deep depression. The maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla were advised to show distant warning signal number one instead of two. The cyclone developing over the south and adjoining southeast Bay of Bengal, moved south and southwestward. It was centred about 1,690 kilometres south-southwest of Chittagong port, 1,690 kms south-southwest of Cox's Bazar port and 1,580 kms south-southwest of Mongla port at 7am, said a Met Department bulletin. It is likely to intensify further, moving in a south-southwesterly direction and cross the Tamilnadu coast, said the bulletin. Maximum sustained wind speed within 48 kms of the storm centre was about 50 kph rising to 60 kph in gusts/ squalls. The sea will remain rough near the stormy zone, warned the weather office. All fishing boats and trawlers over the north Bay and deep sea were advised to remain close to the coast and proceed with caution till further notice. 
